---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---
<MainLayout
  title="About StarterAquarium"
  description="How StarterAquarium researches beginner aquarium gear: published specs, aggregated verified-buyer reviews, independent sources, and use-case fit."
>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc-header">
      <span class="doc-kicker">About</span>
      <h1>About StarterAquarium</h1>
      <p class="doc-lede">
        StarterAquarium is an independent site that compares beginner aquarium gear
        by spec and use case, so your first tank is one your fish actually thrive in.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>
      We cover the gear: tanks and all-in-one kits, filters, heaters, lighting,
      water care, and the food and fun extras. We rank the gear for the person
      setting up their first freshwater tank. Every piece starts from one
      question: who is this actually the right fit for?
    </p>

    <h2>How we research</h2>
    <p>
      Our recommendations are research-based. We synthesize three kinds of
      evidence into use-case-fit picks:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Published specifications.</strong> Manufacturer spec sheets,
        flow rates, wattage, listed tank-size ranges, and rated figures, read
        carefully and compared across brands.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aggregated verified-buyer reviews.</strong> Patterns across owner
        reviews on Amazon and hobbyist forums, including the critical ones, cited
        to their source.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Independent sources.</strong> Write-ups and testing from outlets
        like Aquarium Co-Op and Prime Time Aquatics, cited where we lean on them.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We do not claim personal hands-on testing in our content. We are explicit
      about that. If you want a first-person review, look for a reviewer who claims
      one. What we offer instead is careful comparison: spec analysis, aggregated
      owner reports, and honest use-case fit. You can read exactly how we weigh a
      product on our <a href="/how-we-evaluate/">how we evaluate</a> page.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      We earn affiliate commissions when you buy through our links. It does not
      change the price you pay, and it does not change which product we recommend.
      We do not accept payment in exchange for positive coverage. Full details are
      in our <a href="/disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Specs change and listings drift. If something is out of date or wrong, tell
      us on the <a href="/contact/">contact</a> page and we will fix it.
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .doc { max-width: var(--content-wide); margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6) var(--space-20); }
  .doc-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .doc-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-brass);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .doc-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .doc h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-forest);
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .doc p { line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .doc ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: var(--space-5) 0; }
  .doc li {
    padding: 16px 22px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-brass);
    border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .doc li strong { color: var(--color-forest); }
</style>
